<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,324,594,620]" box="[189,324,594,620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,594,620]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,594,620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,640,737]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The genus name, a feminine Latin noun, combines 
<emphasis box="[810,881,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">brevis</emphasis>
(“short”), 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1123,640,666]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aphrodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1012,1123,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Aphrodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the name of a related extant leafhopper genus), and - 
<emphasis box="[555,599,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">ella</emphasis>
(a diminutive suffix), refering to the small size and short forewings of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
